{
  "texts": [
    "T he digital age presents both opportunities for and challenges to science communication.",
    "Communication hubs such as Twitter, Facebook, and YouTube offer unprecedented reach for scientific content and interaction with the public (Collins et al. 2016), thereby making science more accessible for scientists and laypeople alike.",
    "With engagement tools such as likes, dislikes, comments, and shares, members of the general public now no longer simply consume scientific content but can also disseminate it.",
    "As a result, scientific content that does not engage the public may never reach a large audience.",
    "In the oversaturated and highly competitive environment of social media, how can scientists make their voices heard?"
  ]
}